  let _ = w f "<div class='section-sub'>Rail teaches itself. Think of training an apprentice cook: give them a recipe, they try it, the oven decides if it worked. Keep what worked, use it in tomorrow's lesson. Do it a thousand times. Rail does this with code &mdash; and the oven is the compiler. If the compiler runs it, the code is right. No human has to grade anything.</div>"

